text: TBH, these scenes were the best the film had to offer. I'm a bit disappointed actually, because 'Zootopia' and 'Inside Out' had given me the impression that animated films had finally got out of the rut they'd been stuck in, but 'The Secret Life of Pets' was a step backwards in my opinion. It's basically 'Garfield' with some elements of 'Oliver & Company' and 'Stuart Little' thrown in.  I hope the next animation will make up for this.
